						               													<description>This game consists of collecting animals that belong to the same family and accumulate the most points according to the way they are played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The deck consists in 38 cards (36 native animals and 2 rules cards).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each card includes the name of the species, the family it belongs, the number of members of that family and the points it's worth.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to collect points? There are 3 ways:&amp;#10;1. Reuniting an incomplete family, you obtain the sum of the points of the cards played.&amp;#10;2. Reuniting a complete family on the board, on different turns, you obtain the sum of the points of the cards + points indicated on the bonus card.&amp;#10;3. Reuniting a complete family in one turn, you obtain double points (from played cards + bonus)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of the game each player has 5 cards, on each turn there are two phases:&amp;#10;1. Draw a card from the deck or discard pile and play a family (complete or incomplete).&amp;#10;2a. Say it's the end of the turn turn.&amp;#10;2b. Or the player can discard a card from the hand, then asking to opponent if he has a card that can be used to complete a family: if he does, he must give it to the player; if he doesn't, the player loses the discarded card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of the next turn, each player starts draw to complete a hand of 5 cards and start again until the deck is depleted.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
